Review:
We enjoyed our stay!

The neighborhood is great, with a pretty and safe atmosphere;
The apartment is very pretty and clean, the living room and porch really make a difference;
The room is good, I wish it was quieter and the bed was bigger though (not in a bad way, Tessa told me ahead of time that it's a twin-size bed. It's perfect for one person, not two. It wasn't a big deal though; the room is next to a busy road so I could hear trucks and cars during sleep).

Overall, the room is really cool. This is my first time using Airbnb. I really loved it. It's way better than any hotel. I felt at home and Trevor helped us get to know the real local stuff. I will definitely book it again! Thanks again, Tessa & Trevor!

The unit is nicely set up;
The neighborhood is great -- lots of great places to eat, and do other things;
Close to Mont Royal;
I highly recommend this place and if I have a future occasion to be in Montreal, I will definitely try to book here again.

We met Andrea and Robin when we left, and it "clicked" right away. They seem very nice, and we felt right at home in their apartment; 
Apart from the fridge, the bathroom, and the bedroom in the basement that we had to clean up on arrival, the apartment is spacious with a large garden and two bedrooms. Kitchen, dining room, and living room. However, the fact that it wasn't completely renovated made our stay more comfortable for the kids... 
The situation is not bad, but with little ones, it was quite isolated and a bit far from dense areas of activities. I loved the Italian grocery store two blocks away from the house!
